STRATEGY_ID: Internal PSV001,Internal PSV002,Internal PSV003A,Internal PSV003B,Internal PSV004
DESCRIPTION: PSV failure due to corrosion, fouling, solids etc

CREDIBLE_NOTES: Condenser Cooler Tube side has hot acid gases being cooled with cooling water on the shell side. Hot tube inlet regions where condensed-acid formation and revaporization occurs are highly susceptible to acid corrosion, these regions are generally little further away from tube-sheet. Similarly, channel barrel to tube sheet weld in inlet chamber is susceptible to corrosion due to condensate pooling around the barrel perimeter.
Corrosion of Free Iron on 304L is common due to rub-off from ordinary carbon steel or low alloy steel during material fabrication or handling process.
Vessel s insulated top section construction material is Titanium, Titanium has excellent resistance to Corrosion under Insulation hence susceptibility to CUI is negligible.
STRATEGY_NOTES: 8Y CUI Inspection Interval strategy suggested for Vessel Top Head, no strategy exists presently.

CREDIBLE_NOTES: In inlet chamber the top-tubesheet (material SS 304L) is bonded to the top-head cone (material Titanium) with Titanium weld overlay on stainless steel, the weld is susceptible to dissimilar metal disbonding.
Vessel s mid and bottom sections construction material is CRA SS 304L and operating mostly in dry conditions, hence not susceptible to external surface corrosion.
Vessel has cooling water on the shell side. During upset conditions of cooling water chemical treatment, SS304L is susceptible to Microbiologically Influenced Corrosion.

Weld decay/intergranular stress corrosion cracking in Heat Affected Zone and due to acid-condensate pooling around Channel barrel to Tubesheet weld perimeter in inlet chamber during temperature upsets.

DESCRIPTION: PSV failure due to corrosion, fouling, solids etc
